https://review.openstack.org/107027 which at this stage is just WIP, changes the server address output so it looks something like:

        "addresses": {
            "private": [
                {
                    "addr": "10.0.0.2", 
                    "label": "private", 
                    "version": 4
                }
            ], 
            "public": [
                {
                    "addr": "172.24.4.1", 
                    "label": "private", 
                    "version": 4
                }, 
            ]
        }, 

eg we list private (fixed) ip addresses separately from public (floating ips). And each ip address has a label which corresponds to the name of the network it belongs to. I think this will be less confusing even though we still have a public ip with the label of "private"
